metadata.name: Birthday
metadata.description:
Had the best birthday in years. I'm not a birthday-type-of-person, but Ava made my day awesome. She prepared very delicious Italian food and made me a big cake herself. The cake ended up taste like cookie and was really hard to cut, but it was very nice cookie still. 

Also my killer MacBook Pro finally arrived. I placed the order in the early December. Took a long time for Apple to ship. It is almost full-spec: 64GB Ram, lots of neural engines and lots of cores, I almost opted for 8TB storage, but figured I would never store so much stuff on a singe machine. So I ended up with 4TB (still an overkill for programmer). I'm still migrating my work to the new machine. There's some hiccups. I cannot npm install canvas due to some obscure issue, but so far I'm very impressed by the machine.

Fixed an animation problem with my Mementos project. Previously characters would not automatically break lines if you increase font size. Number of characters in each line remains the same, so the line becomes longer and goes out of screen width, which is stupid. I fixed that. I also added a progress bar to the bottom. I don't like the idea so much. It's too distracting. So I made it such that user can only see it when he scrolls down.

Ava suggests allowing user to control the progress bar, just like a video player. I thought about it and decided against it. It would ruin the flow of organic movement. If user is out of time, the most compromise I can do is let him speed up the playback, which is already implemented. If he really wants to jump to a certain position to read something, he can always refer to the text, without breaking the animation's organics.

Also added a 5-seconds wait after animation completes, before restarting all over. This adds a nice touch to signal the end of the script.
